    <h1>Widgets</h1>
    <h2>Here are widgets you may embed in your website</h2>
    <p>(not actively being worked on, don't expect more for now)</p>
    <h3>wGrid Widget</h3>
    <iframe src="/widgets/wGrid/?theme=dark" height="300"></iframe>
    <h4>How to Embed?</h4>
    <code>&lt;iframe src="https://c48.uk/widgets/wGrid/" height="300"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</code>
    <p>Then, you have to specify a query URL parameter based on the theme. <code>?theme=dark</code> or
        <code>?theme=light</code></p>
    <p>So, for example, the whole URL could be <code>https://c48.uk/widgets/wGrid/?theme=dark</code>
    </p>
    <p>If you don't, well...</p>
    <iframe src="/widgets/wGrid/" style="background-color: white;" height="300"></iframe>
    <script is:inline src="https://a.c48.uk/bacon.js"></script>
</body>